    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">The Hague explosion</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-9-1.jpg" alt="The Hague explosion" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">At least five people have been <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/12/08/at-least-five-killed-after-explosion-rips-through-apartment-in-dutch-city-the-hague" target=="_blank">killed</a> in a devastating explosion that leveled an entire apartment block in The Hague, Netherlands. Emergency responders acted swiftly, managing to rescue four individuals from the debris; however, it remains uncertain how many others might still be trapped inside the wreckage. Investigators are currently exploring the circumstances surrounding the explosion, mainly focusing on identifying a suspicious vehicle that was seen speeding away from the scene immediately after the blast occurred.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">As search and rescue efforts carry on, authorities are now focusing on salvage operations to assess damage and recover any remaining individuals. About 40 nearby apartments have been evacuated for resident safety. A specialized rescue team with prior experience in Türkiye's 2023 earthquakes has been deployed to aid recovery. Prime Minister Dick Schoof <a href="https://twitter.com/MinPres/status/1865329825193271362?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1865329825193271362%7Ctwgr%5E0df8e288a5f86c7be3b7579f7a5cda4d180905fc%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euronews.com%2Fmy-europe%2F2024%2F12%2F08%2Fat-least-five-killed-after-explosion-rips-through-apartment-in-dutch-city-the-hague" target=="_blank">said</a>, “My thoughts go out to the victims, all other people involved, and the emergency services who are now working on the scene.”</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Space Odyssey</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-9-2.jpg" alt="Space Odyssey" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">Jared Isaacman, CEO of Shift4 Payments and a prominent figure in private spaceflight, has been <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/06/science/nasa-chief-trump-pick-jared-isaacman/index.html" target=="_blank">nominated</a> by President-elect Trump as NASA Administrator. Isaacman, known for founding and leading the historic <a href="https://inspiration4.com/mission" target=="_blank">Inspiration4</a> space mission with SpaceX, brings a blend of entrepreneurial and spaceflight experience. He would succeed outgoing NASA administrator <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people/nasa-administrator-bill-nelson/" target=="_blank">Bill Nelson</a>, a former space shuttle astronaut and Democratic senator for Florida appointed by Joe Biden in 2021.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);"> However, concerns have risen over his close ties with SpaceX and Elon Musk, raising potential conflicts of interest as NASA collaborates extensively with private companies. This position is also usually given to a scientist or aerospace engineer rather than a businessman. Isaacman’s vision for NASA, emphasizing commercial partnerships and extraterrestrial exploration, may reshape the agency’s direction amid ongoing challenges like the <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/humans-in-space/artemis/" target=="_blank">Artemis program</a> and the <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/reference/space-launch-system/" target=="_blank">Space Launch System</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
